	<article class="post-89059 post type-post status-publish hentry category-dashboard tag-entrepreneurship tag-small-business des-entrepreneurship des-small-business news_keywords-entrepreneurship news_keywords-small-business-2" id="post-89059">
	<header class="postHeader">
				<div class="postKicker">
					</div>
				<h1 itemprop="headline" class="entry-title">Today in Small Business: The Coolest New Businesses in Brooklyn</h1>
		<div class="story-meta-footer">
			<address class="byline author vcard" itemprop="author creator" itemtype="//schema.org/Person">
				By Gene Marks			</address>
			<!-- date published --><time class="dateline " datetime="2014-10-02T16:49:06+00:00" itemprop="datePublished">October 2, 2014 12:49 pm</time>
			<!-- date updated --><span class="visually-hidden updated">October 2, 2014 12:49 pm</span><button class="button comments-button  theme-kicker" data-skip-to-para-id="">
</button>
		</div>
			</header>
		<div class="entry-content"><div id="sharetools-story" class="sharetools theme-classic sharetools-story" data-shares="email|Email,facebook|Share,twitter|Tweet,save|Save,show-all|More,ad" data-url="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/10/02/today-in-small-business-the-coolest-new-businesses-in-brooklyn/" data-title="Today in Small Business: The Coolest New Businesses in Brooklyn" data-description="Uber for Business. How to work from home more effectively. Is it legal for bosses to use social media tools to check backgrounds when hiring?">
				<div class="ad sharetools-inline-article-ad"></div>
				<div id="MiddleLeft" class="ad middle-left-ad nocontent robots-nocontent"></div>
				</div><div class="inlineModule"><div class="entry"><h6 class="kicker"><a href="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/category/dashboard/">Dashboard</a></h6><p class="summary">A daily roundup of small-business developments.</p></div></div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Whatâs affecting me, my clients and other small-business owners today.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>The Economy</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>America&#8217;s manufacturing industry <a href="//www.cnbc.com/id/101906427#.">expanded in</a> September.</li>
<li>The middle class is <a href="//www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/wonkblog/wp/2014/10/01/the-middle-class-is-poorer-today-than-it-was-in-1989/">poorer today</a> than it was in 1989.</li>
<li>The growth of auto and truck sales slowed after a blistering August but <a href="//abcnews.go.com/Business/wireStory/truck-deals-boost-us-auto-sales-september-25886094">is closer to</a> what analysts are predicting for the full year.</li>
<li>Foreign investment in <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/10/02/business/owning-a-piece-of-america.html">American real estate</a> is taking off again.</li>
<li>Those who <a href="//www.bloomberg.com/news/2014-10-02/fed-critics-say-10-letter-warning-inflation-still-right.html">predicted inflation</a> in 2010 say they were right.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Around the Country</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Here are the <a href="//www.businessinsider.com/coolest-new-small-businesses-in-brooklyn-2014-9?op=1">coolest new businesses</a> in Brooklyn.</li>
<li>Filing fees for new Colorado businesses <a href="//www.bizjournals.com/denver/news/2014/10/01/colorado-new-business-filing-fee-holiday-to.html">will remain</a> at the low, low price of $1 for at least the rest of this month.</li>
<li>A âShadow Shark Tankâ sweepstakes in select states <a href="//www.midweeknews.com/articles/2014/09/25/3d46c7fd883c48828bdb60e34bf2bcc2/index.xml">will provide</a> one winner the opportunity to spend the day on the set of the show.</li>
<li>Uber for Business <a href="//thenextweb.com/insider/2014/10/01/uber-business-arrives-200-cities/">arrives in</a> more than 200 cities.</li>
<li>New Yorkâs mayor announced the start of Digital.NYC, a hub <a href="//money.cnn.com/2014/10/01/technology/digital-nyc-startups/index.html">for all things</a> related to the New York City start-up ecosystem.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Around the World</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The Nobel laureate Joseph E. Stiglitz says austerity has been an â<a href="//www.theguardian.com/business/2014/oct/01/austerity-eurozone-disaster-joseph-stiglitz">utter disaster</a>â for the Eurozone.</li>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"> <span id="more-89059"></span>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Ideas</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>This company <a href="//www.slate.com/blogs/moneybox/2014/10/01/enviroflight_ohio_company_produces_fly_larvae_to_bring_down_costs_of_fish.html">wants to fight</a> world hunger with flies.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Management</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>James Altucher says most leadership advice is useless and shares what he <a href="//www.entrepreneur.com/article/237863">really learned</a> running 20 companies.</li>
<li>Here are 53 <a href="//blog.directcapital.com/business-insights/small-biz-news/business-plan-resources/?">useful business plan</a> resources.</li>
<li>Here&#8217;s how to <a href="//blogs.hbr.org/2014/10/5-ways-to-work-from-home-more-effectively/">work from home</a> more effectively.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Employees</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Is it legal for bosses to use social media tools to <a href="//www.nfib.com/article/the-legality-of-using-social-media-tools-when-hiring-mybiz-so2014-66433/">check backgrounds when hiring?</a></li>
<li>As <a href="//www.foxbusiness.com/markets/2014/10/01/as-more-workers-quit-small-businesses-are-working-to-keep-top-talent-from/">more workers quit</a>, many small businesses are working harder to keep talent from leaving.</li>
<li>Silicon Valley is taking the &#8220;<a href="//www.nytimes.com/reuters/2014/10/02/technology/02reuters-tech-benefits.html">benefits arm race</a>&#8221; to health care.</li>
<li>While the restaurant industry fights efforts to increase the minimum wage, a survey shows that 83 percent of restaurant patrons <a href="//news.yahoo.com/u-restaurant-patrons-support-minimum-wage-hike-survey-204419834--finance.html?">support raising</a> it.</li>
<li>Women <a href="//www.aei-ideas.org/2014/10/women-earned-majority-of-doctoral-degrees-in-2013-for-5th-straight-year-and-outnumber-men-in-grad-school-137-5-to-100/?">earned the majority</a> of doctoral degrees in 2013 for the fifth straight year (but <a href="//thinkprogress.org/economy/2014/10/01/3574394/women-venture-capital-funding/">start-up funding</a> is given almost entirely to men).</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Online</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Reddit secures <a href="//www.theguardian.com/technology/2014/oct/01/reddit-secures-50m-fundraising-investors-snoop-dogg?C">$50 million in fund-raising</a> from investors including Snoop Dogg, and users <a href="//time.com/3453422/reddit-shares/">may get</a> free shares of the website.</li>
<li>Google makes <a href="//venturebeat.com/2014/10/01/googles-back-with-more-cloud-price-cuts/">more cuts</a> to its cloud pricing.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Marketing</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A survey <a href="//finance.yahoo.com/news/survey-pinpoints-top-priorities-converting-192018089.html?">suggests ways to convert</a> website visits from millennials into sales.</li>
<li>Here are 10 simple ways to <a href="//small-bizsense.com/invoices-for-marketing/">transform invoices</a> into marketing machines.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Entrepreneurship</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A Winnipeg entrepreneur bets the farm on that &#8220;<a href="//www.theglobeandmail.com/report-on-business/small-business/sb-growth/the-challenge/entrepreneur-bets-the-farm-on-that-other-black-gold/article20854910/">other black gold</a>&#8221; (specialized compost).</li>
<li>Here are some tips on <a href="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/10/01/how-to-be-an-entrepreneur-and-stay-married/?_">how to be</a> an entrepreneur, and stay married.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Start-Up</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Digital health start-ups <a href="//recode.net/2014/10/01/digital-health-startups-raised-700-million-during-third-quarter/">raised $700 million</a> during the third quarter.</li>
<li>Derek Jeter announces an <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/10/02/sports/baseball/derek-jeter-outlines-digital-venture-a-publishing-outlet-for-athletes.html">entrepreneurial venture</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Social Media</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Hundreds of people have <a href="//www.thetelegram.com/Business/2014-09-30/article-3888011/%26lsquo%3bSexist%26rsquo%3b-baby-PJs-target-of-Twitter-outcry/1">denounced Target</a> for selling âsexistâ baby pajamas.</li>
<li>Twitter says it will <a href="//www.bizjournals.com/boston/blog/techflash/2014/10/twitter-to-invest-10m-in-mit-social-media-research.html?page=all">invest $10 million</a> in a social media research lab at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Technology</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Microsoft says its new Office app will <a href="//www.informationweek.com/software/productivity-collaboration-apps/microsoft-sway-aims-to-simplify-presentation-creation/d/d-id/1316230">help you build</a> beautiful, interactive presentations even if you have no design skills.</li>
<li>A survey of 2,000 consumers finds <a href="//www.cnbc.com/id/102049037">more than half</a> are ready to take their business elsewhere after a data breach.</li>
<li>Apple will <a href="//www.bloomberg.com/news/2014-10-01/apple-said-to-add-gold-option-to-ipad-to-goose-sales.html">add a gold color option</a> for its full-size iPads.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><em>Gene Marks owns the <a href="//www.marksgroup.net">Marks Group</a>, a Bala Cynwyd, Pa., consulting firm that helps clients with customer relationship management. You can follow him on <a href="https://www.twitter.com/genemarks">Twitter</a>.</em></p>
